links.evidence: The model describing the docking molecules indicated that all of the 17 compounds in the garlic essential oil from T1-ACE2 to T17-ACE2 have the binding ability toward the areas affected by the ACE2 protein.
The compounds T1 and T2 indicated the highest content in the garlic essential oil (51.3%) and gave the best anti-SARS-CoV-2 activity, followed by the three compounds T5, T4, and T11.
